This repo's coding rules are canonical in [CLAUDE.md](mdc:CLAUDE.md) and mirrored in
[AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md). Read one before changing code. Highlights:

- **The seam:** agent-awareness lives ONLY in `adapters/`; `core/` is a pure source-agnostic reducer
  over the `core/events.ts` contract. The app imports only `core/state` (type-only) + `core/events`.
- **Runtime deps = `bun` + `jq` only.** No runtime npm packages.
- **TypeScript:** arrow-`const` functions (never `function` decls), `interface I*` / `type T*`, no
  `any`, string enums (never bare `"a" | "b"` unions), braces on every `if`/`else`, kebab-case files.
  Bun doesn't type-check — run `bunx tsc --noEmit`.
- **Hook scripts (`adapters/*/hooks/*.sh`):** never write stdout, always `exit 0`, append-only one
  journal file per session, build JSON via `jq`, no network. Multi-field parse uses `IFS=$'\002'` +
  jq `join("")` (visible escapes, never a raw control byte).
- **Tests:** `bun test`. Hook scripts are tested by spawning the real script against fixture JSON.
- **Commits:** Conventional Commits; one logical change each.
